reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This was my second MSI motherboard and I have found they are easy to work with, fit all the components well, and perform well. As an avid gamer and computer enthusiast, I'm always on the lookout for high-quality components to enhance my gaming experience, and this motherboard delivers on all fronts. The MSI MAG B760M Mortar WiFi II Gaming Motherboard is a true powerhouse that delivers unparalleled performance, reliability, and customization options.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Single USB 3.0 header was my only disappointment.
reviews.reviewText: I originally planned on putting this in a Lian Li Mesh mATX case, but then I bought the 14900kf. Well it's in a much larger Deepcool case now. That case has two USB 3.0 19/20 pin header cables and this board only has one header :( even my older Prime B660M-A D4 has two usb 3.0 headers. But this case has 3 m.2 slots so I used one for a m.2 USB 3.0 Header card.The MSI software is less invasive than Asus, or Gigabyte, also the BIOS is pretty easy to deal with.There is a fair amount of available high speed approved ram if you search, but my first set of approved X-DATA 6400mhz RAM had a bad stick. Trying Patriot 7000mhz next.It's a fine mATX board, I would prefer this over any ASUS. Also looks good with my MSI GPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Returned, quit booting to OS
reviews.reviewText: Everything was good. I loaded a copy of Windows 10 Pro on. It booted to win 10 twice, then I wanted to upgrade it to win 11. It did not go into to boot screen, so I restarted and went into bios. Sometimes I could get into bios and sometimes I could not. No matter what I did, it would not boot to a drive. Not a hard drive or a DVD drive. I trouble shot the memory, no difference. I removed to boot drive and replaced with three different hard drives and it still would not boot to a drive so I could install an operating system. I have built dozens of computers and never had this problem. So I tore it down and returned it. On a good point, I was reimbursed the full amount. On a side note, I got a different board and it is installed and happily running windows 11. It was definitely a bad motherboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It arrived earlier than expected, the packaging arrived in good condition, so far everything is going well. The good thing about this board is that it has one more slot with a heatsink compared to the MORTAR, and it also has the QLEDs that warn of any failure. The only bad thing is how difficult it is to handle the installation, there is little space to install the other components.

I tried to install the latest model of Samsung & WD M2 SSDs on this MB. None of them can be recognized. When I tried to return this immature product, I found it was shipped by Canada Direct, not Amazon. The return process is a terrible nightmare. And Canada Direct partially refunded me 80% only. I learned 2 painful lessons from this purchase: (1) Never consider MSI product any more in the future; (2) Pay attention to the shipper. If it’s Canada Direct, not Amazon, do NOT place order, forget it!

Muy buena Motherboard. Pude instalar mi Intel core i5-14600k sin ningún problema, no se necesita actualizar la BIOS. La Motherboard es de muy buena calidad y tiene lo último en tecnología. La recomiendo ampliamente.
Just built a new pc with a 14th gen I9, everything work well except the motherboard does not support the CPU. The box only says 12-13. This is false advertisement
